article_title: Boeing Suppliers Use Ukrainian-Built Cargo Jets to Keep Supplies Flowing
article_text:
Boeing Co. and its suppliers have turned to giant, Ukrainian-made cargo jets to keep its supply chain running smoothly, partially in response to disruptions at U.S. West coast ports from a recent labor dispute there.

The aerospace giant’s top commercial-airplane executive on Tuesday said disruptions have continued even after the parties in that disagreement reached a deal earlier this month. A Boeing spokesman said separately that...
